Gold Price in Hong Kong Up 
The gold price in Hong Kong went up eight HK dollars to close at 2,600
HK dollars a tael today, according to Po Sang Bank, one of the major
gold dealers in Hong Kong.
The gold price is equivalent to 280.42 U.S. dollars a troy ounce, 0.85
U.S. dollars up from the previous close, at today' s exchange rate of
one U.S. dollar against 7.7830 HK dollars.
